In commemoration of this year’s World Health Day with the theme; ‘Our Planet, Our Health, the African Youth Growth Foundation (AYGF) has harped on increased awareness on the prevention of harmful practices that affect climate change in Nigeria through mass mobilization and sensitization of grass root communities, as part of behavior change communication and launched the Earth Restoration Campaign-Nigeria. The executive director, Dr Arome Salifu, disclosed this at a press conference to mark the day. Salifu stated that there was need for  concerted efforts to be directed towards attitudinal change and increase awareness as Nigeria’s environment is under increasing threat from human activities and natural disasters which is evident with adverse effects of climate change. He said the Earth Restoration Campaign’ ERC-Nigeria was intended to build partnership with relevant stakeholders on the campaign to increase awareness of harmful practices that affect climate change in Nigeria and to build on enhancing the implementation of the Nigeria Climate Change Policy Response and Strategy (NCCPRS), approved by the Federal Executive Council in the year 2012 which is a comprehensive strategy policy on climate change.